Engr. Rasheed Teslim Balo­gun, governorship aspirant of the Peoples Democratic Party(PDP) in Lagos State, has joined several eminent Nigerians to commiserate with the Oyo State Gover­nor, Engr. Seyi Makinde on the death of the Olubadan of Ibadanland, Oba Saliu Akanmu Adetunji,(Aje Ogugunuso 1), saying the monarch’s death had left a void in the ranks of the traditional institution in Yorubaland. Engr. Balogun, in his con­dolence message, described the death of the monarch as a big loss to sons and daughters of Ibadan land, saying Oba Adetunji’s imprints in the development of the ancient town would be remembered for a very long time. The PDP hopeful in Lagos state also sent his condolence message to the Olubadan-in Council, adding that the council had lost a mature and peaceful man whose five-year reign was adjudged the most peaceful in Ibadan history. Barber Stabs Motorcyclist To Death In Bayelsa Novena University College Of Law Commences LL.B Degree… “Oba Adetunji lived a ful­filled life and his contribu­tions to the wellbeing of the people of Ibadan was a testi­mony of his exemplary life. We can also remember Baba for his courage, consistency, humility and sense of hones­ty. The late Olubadan, in his lifetime, was a unifying factor, a rallying figure whose large heart was highly remarkable. “The late monarch lived a worthy life by putting the interest of the Ibadan people first before others.